Package: multibayes
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Multiplicity Adjustment via Prior Odds
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Margherita", "Calderan", 
           email = "margherita.calderan@gmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-5668-5162"))
Description: Implements Bayesian multiplicity adjustment by calibrating
    hypothesis-specific prior odds from a global prior probability assigned to
    the complete null across a family of tests. The resulting adjusted prior
    odds can be combined with Bayes factors to produce multiplicity-adjusted
    posterior odds while retaining interpretability. The package also provides
    an adjustment for probability of direction (pd) when users place priors for
    parameter estimates centered on the tested null value.
